The paper deals with the equivalence of two-way and one-way finite state transducers, which is a fundamental concept in formal language theory and automata theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). The paper also involves the decidability of a definability problem, which is related to information theory, so cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a likely category. The proof techniques used in the paper involve logical reasoning and model theory, which are related to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also involves algorithms and computational complexity, which are related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper deals with the expressive power of transducers, which is related to cs.PL (Programming Languages).
